added.title: Real Art
added.description: After Starfire buys an ugly painting, the Titans take her to the museum so she can experience real art.

added.title: Just a Little Patience…Yeah…Yeah
added.description: Robin tries to teach the other Titans to have patience.

added.title: The Fight
added.description: Robin tries to teach the other Titans about real estate, but they're only interested in finding a villain to fight.

added.title: The Chaff
added.description: In an effort to get Teen Titan Go! canceled, Control Freak shows off some deleted scenes.

added.title: The Bergerac
added.description: The Titans give Robin advice to guide him through his camp romance with Wonder Girl.

added.title: The Kitty
added.description: After a mishap in the forest, the Bears lose their own home to dangerous animals.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Tubin'
added.description: In search of some adventure, the Bears ride a tube down a dangerous river.

added.title: Vacation
added.description: Nom Nom is ordered by his doctor to take a vacation. But he's paired with an unlikely travel buddy- Grizz.

added.title: The Park
added.description: The Bears spend a day at the park. Grizz works out. Panda attempts to sell his artwork. Ice Bear trains some kids.

added.title: The Master
added.description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: The Move
added.description: Clayton is a compulsive liar, but Gumball discovers he wasn't lying about his awesome martial arts move. Gumball confronts Clayton about his fabled Seven Pressure Point Heart Exploding Technique, assuming it's another one of his outlandish claims. Darwin and Gumball intervene to help Clayton start embracing the truth. However, when they discover the move is as effective as he claimed, they really wish he'd been lying.

added.title: The Mothers
added.description: It's Mother's Day and kids put their moms through a series of tests to determine who has the World's Greatest Mom.  It's Mother's Day, and Gumball and Darwin discover that Tobias and Banana Joe have both made a card for "The Best Mom in the World". Clearly Nicole Watterson is the Best Mom, but Tobias and BJ just won't admit it... So they organise a mom-off at the mall between Nicole, Banana Barbara and Jackie Wilson. Needless to say it gets pretty intense.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: Heads of the Family
added.description: Team Tennyson stops in at a fringe family reunion, and Ben encounters a whole lot more than kooky cousins namely, Kevin 11 and the Bugg Brothers, whose latest crackpot invention sparks a series of hilarious head-swaps between all parties.

added.title: Wheels of Fortune
added.description: Team Tennyson's thrift store shopping is ruined by the latest high-speed heist of LaGrange — who is now aided by a super-fast electromagnetic racing car — and Ben must convince Kevin 11 to help stop the speed demon's globetrotting robbing spree.

added.title: Vin Diagram
added.description: When Ben sees Vin Ethanol impressed with Kevin's automotive know-how, Ben's jealousy has him convinced that he has to out-do Kevin before the older boy influences Vin to embrace his bad-guy side at a charity race.

added.title: What Rhymes with Omnitrix?
added.description: At a poetry slam event, Charmcaster's reading of Kevin's poetry causes magical trouble for Ben and Gwen, causing mind swaps that have everyone confused as to who's fighting who.

added.title: Adrenaland Jr.
added.description: Team Tennyson visits the safety-neutered version of Adrenaland known as "Adrenaland Jr.", only to end up facing off against a bitter Kevin 11, out to destroy everyone else's good, and safe, time.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: The End Was Here
added.description: Craig tries to figure out how an ancient war that decimated the Creek began in hopes of stopping history from repeating itself.

added.title: The Children of the Dog
added.description: Craig has tried to convince his family to get a dog for years but has never been successful, but he may have a chance if he follows the guidance of a charismatic creek kid and her three step program.

added.title: Encore'tney
added.description: When Courtney turns to a magical datebook to help her achieve perfection, she's trapped in a never ending loop until a friend teaches her a valuable lesson.

added.title: Life of Pie
added.description: When Izzy, Jude and Owen accidentally bring a pizza to life they do everything they can to help him find a new purpose in life other than being eaten.

added.title: Snots Landing
added.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: A Licking Time Bomb
added.description: Owen and Noah unwittingly become cookie moguls and must hide the secret ingredient, which is Owen's spit from licking the sprinkles off the cookies.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Hot Wings
added.description: A lemur belonging to the Duchess' adventurous cousin puts Tom's job as Under-Butler in jeopardy.

added.title: Wild Goose Chase
added.description: The detectives agree to escort a goofy Canadian goose back across the border before duck hunting season begins.

added.title: Play Date with Destiny
added.description: A wild chase leads Jerry into the arms of a little girl and now Tom has to help Jerry escape her clutches.

added.title: Mind Your Royal Manners
added.description: Fearful that he will lose his place in the Manor, Tom adopts the attitude of a member of the Royal Guard in order to keep the mice and their new friend, Boswell, from wreaking havoc in the kitchen.

added.title: A Rare Breed
added.description: Jerry is mistaken for a rare breed of Guinea Pig by the Duchess' professor friend and uses his protected, elevated status to create endless problems for Tom.

added.title: Powerless
added.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

added.title: Ancient History
added.description: While Aspheera pursues revenge on the "Treacherous Deceiver" who betrayed her, the ninja make a startling discovery.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 1
added.description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

added.title: #FreshPrincessOfRenFaire Part 2
added.description: A fun day at the Renaissance Faire takes a dark turn when our heroes clash with a princess-eating dragon.

added.title: Eclipsorr
added.description: Third Earth's sun is being blocked out by the Eclipsor Corporation, an amoral company that wants to sell its energy for a profit. The ThunderCats can't do anything about it because they don't have a spaceship, yet!

added.title: Wizz-Ra
added.description: The ThunderCats freak out when a spooky ghost dressed like a pharaoh appears in their mirrors! They quickly set about to getting rid of every reflective surface in their lair, because that ghost is scary and no one wants to talk to him!

added.title: ThunderDogs
added.description: The Thundercats agree to foster a demonic puppy from the Astral Plane until they can find it the perfect owner. But could the perfect owner be their worst enemy? Their worst enemy is Mumm-Ra in case you forgot!

added.title: Mini Mongor
added.description: The Thunderkittens unleash a demon who is powered by fear. Too bad he's small and not that scary.

added.title: Swampy Johnny
added.description: The Thundercats invite a super cool swamp man into the Cat's Lair who is on the run from some scary looking aliens!

added.title: Rose's Room
added.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

added.title: Steven and the Stevens
added.description: Steven needs a musical partner for an upcoming show, and uses a time travel device to recruit the perfect bandmate, HIMSELF!

added.title: Space Race
added.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

added.title: Secret Team
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Pearl accidentally pop a bubbled gem and form Secret Team to secretly retrieve the missing shards.

added.title: Rose's Scabbard
added.description: Steven joins Pearl on a special mission to a place that belonged to Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Captured Clops
added.description: Badgerclops is tired of his responsibilities at Sheriff's HQ, so he joins the Sky Pirates.

added.title: Strange Bedfellows
added.description: After an insane battle, MM and OS end up in the same hospital room. But even in full body casts, the sworn enemies continue the fight.

added.title: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
added.description: Finn and Jake travel to a land where reality has been redesigned and improved.

added.title: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
added.description: While exploring some futuristic ruins, Susan sees glimpses of a familiar girl.

added.title: Islands Part 6: Min & Marty
added.description: An unexpected revelation from Susan leads Finn closer to answers about his past.

added.title: Islands Part 7: Helpers
added.description: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

added.title: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
added.description: Finn confronts the power behind Founders Island, but will he ever return home to Ooo?

added.title: La mascara del engano
added.description: Cuando un sindicato de criminals desconocido amenaza a la Familia Real, los ninjas son llamados de nuevo a la acción y deben proteger a la princesa real y un artefacto legendario que puede tener poderes sobrenaturales.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Mask of Deception
added.description: When an unknown criminal syndicate threatens the Royal Family, the Ninja are called back into action and must protect the royal princess and a fabled artifact that may hold supernatural powers.

added.title: La princesa de jade
added.description: A raíz de un cruel ataque al Palacio, Los Hijos de Garmadon roban la segunda Máscara Oni, y los ninjas invitan a la Princesa Real, Harumi, a su improvisada familia.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Jade Princess
added.description: In the wake of a vicious attack upon the palace, the Sons of Garmadon steal the second Oni Mask, and the ninja invite the royal princess, Harumi, into their makeshift family.

added.title: El oni y el dragon
added.description: Mientras que la Princesa Harumi se adapta a la vida con los ninjas, Lloyd y Jay buscan respuestas sobre las máscaras Oni, mientras que Cole y Zane intentan infiltrarse en Los Hijos de Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Oni & the Dragon
added.description: While Princess Harumi adjusts to life with the ninja, Lloyd and Jay search for answers about the Oni Masks, while Cole and Zane attempt to infiltrate the Sons of Garmadon.

added.title: Guar serpiente
added.description: Para unirse a Los Hijos de Garmadon, Zane (alias Jaguar Serpiente) participa en una carrera de iniciación mortal de motocicletas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Snake Jaguar
added.description: In order to join the Sons of Garmadon, Zane (aka Snake Jaguar) participates in a deadly motorcycle initiation race.

added.title: Local News Legend
added.description: Margaret really wants to host a weekly segment on the nightly local news.

added.title: El chillido de hombre muerto
added.description: La casi desaparición de Zane a manos del Señor "E" obliga a los ninjas a huir a bordo del Bounty, donde descubren que una tramisión que Zane interceptó puede revelar la ubicación oculta del "Silencioso".
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dead Man's Squall
added.description: Zane's near demise at the hands of Mr. E forces the ninja to flee aboard the Bounty, where they discover that a transmission Zane intercepted may reveal the hidden location of the Quiet One.

added.title: Lame Lockdown
added.description: The head scientist puts Mordecai and Rigby on a 24-hour lockdown inside the Dome, but they want to sneak out and see one of their favorite bands.

added.title: El Amo
added.description: Los Watterson juegan un juego de rol fantástico para resolver sus diferencias.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Pelea
added.description: Robin intenta enseñarles a los demás Titanes sobre bienes raíces, pero ellos solamente están interesados en encontrar a un villano con quien enfrentarse.

added.title: Broken Boogie
added.description: When the Boogie Man loses his mojo, Uncle Grandpa steps in to help.

added.title: Cartoon Factory
added.description: Uncle Grandpa visits the cartoon factory to get some answers about his roots.

added.title: Chess Master Steve
added.description: Pizza Steve goes to great lengths in order to beat Mr. Gus at a game of chess.

added.title: Guitar of Rock
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Benson replace an electric guitar signed by a rock star, or Benson's fired.

added.title: La burla
added.description: En un esfuerzo por cancelar "Los Jóvenes Titanes en Acción", Control Fenómeno muestra algunas escenas eliminadas del programa.

added.title: I Like You Hi
added.description: Mordecai has to tell C.J. that his text was auto-corrected to say "I like you."

added.title: Gold Watch
added.description: Benson has to get to work on time so he can win a gold watch.

added.title: El Bergerac
added.description: Los Titanes aconsejan a Robin para guiarlo a través de su romance de campamento con Chica Maravilla.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: Ready to Rumble
added.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

added.title: El gatito
added.description: Luego de un percance en el bosque, los Osos pierden su hogar en manos de unos animales peligrosos.

added.title: El Show de Nom Nom
added.description: Las cosas se complican cuando Nom Nom filma su primer programa de televisión. Los Osos se ofrecen a ayudar y aparecen en el programa.

added.title: Balseando
added.description: En busca de un poco de aventura, los Osos descienden por un río peligroso dentro de un tubo.

added.title: Vacaciones
added.description: El doctor de Nom Nom le ordena tomarse unas vacaciones. Pero debe viajar con un compañero incompatible con él: Pardo.

added.title: El Parque
added.description: Los Osos pasan un día en el parque. Pardo hace ejercicio, Panda intenta vender sus obras de arte y Polar entrena a unos niños.

added.title: Perder la cabeza
added.description: El equipo Tennyson se da una vuelta por una reunión familiar alternativa, y Ben se encuentra con mucho más que primos excéntricos, concretamente con Kevin 11 y los Hermanos Bicho, cuyo último invento alocado desata una serie de intercambios de cabeza divertidísimos entre todos los grupos.

added.title: Diagrama de Vin
added.description: Cuando Ben ve que Vin Etanol se asombra con los conocimientos automovilísticos de Kevin, los celos de Ben lo convencen de que tiene que superar a Kevin antes de que el joven convenza a Vin de adoptar su lado malo en una carrera a beneficio.

added.title: Que Rima Con Omnitrix?
added.description: En un recital de lectura de poesía, Charmcaster lee poemas de Kevin y les causa problemas mágicos a Ben y Gwen cuando produce intercambios mentales que dejan a todos confundidos acerca de quién pelea contra quién.

added.title: Adrenalandia Junior
added.description: El equipo de Tennyson visita la versión segura de Adrenalandia, conocida como "Adrenalandia Jr", y allí terminan enfrentándose a un Kevin 11 amargado y decidido a destruir la diversión segura de todos los demás.

added.title: Neumaticos de la Fortuna
added.description: Las compras en la tienda de segunda mano del equipo Tennyson se ven interrumpidas por el último atraco a alta velocidad de LaGrange -que ahora cuenta con la ayuda de un auto de carreras electromagnético superrápido- y Ben debe convencer a Kevin 11 para que ayude a detener la ola de robos del trotamundos endemoniado con la velocidad.

added.title: Sneaky Peeky
added.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Dullance
added.description: Burned out from having so many adventures, Clarence struggles to sit around and do nothing.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ninos del Perro
added.description: Craig ha intentado que su familia adopte un perro durante años, pero nunca lo logró. Puede que ahora tenga una oportunidad si sigue los consejos de un carismático niño del bosque y su programa de tres pasos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Llego el final
added.description: Craig intenta comprender cómo se desató una antigua antigua que diezmó la población del Arroyo, con la esperanza de evitar que la historia se repita.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Una Nueva Vida
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín abandonan sus hogares y se mudan a la ciudad, donde se conocen por primera vez.

added.title: Seamos Heroes
added.description: Cuando K.O. acompaña a su mamá al trabajo, descubre que la tienda de al lado es su clave para convertirse en un gran héroe.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Let's Be Heroes
added.description: When KO tags along with his mom to work, he discovers the convenience store next door is his key to becoming a great hero.

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: El Dia Divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: Permanent Retirement
added.description: Grandpa, Gwen and Ben visit an old maid relative only to find that her retirement community has been overtaken by a shapeshifting aliens called Limax.

added.title: Jethro Es Tuyo
added.description: iK.O. consigue su primera misión en solitario!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Jethro's All Yours
added.description: KO gets his first solo mission!

added.title: 4 a 1
added.description: El temor de Cebollín a las multitudes amenaza el éxito de su equipo de baloncesto.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: Atrapa la Botella
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín inventan un nuevo juego que atrae una atención inesperada.

added.title: Mr. Moon/What's Wrong with Dan
added.description: Mr. Moon: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox./What's Wrong with Dan: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth- an impostor!

added.title: Impotente
added.description: El ninja corre al Museo de Historia de NINJAGO para recuperar un pergamino peligroso antes de que caiga en manos de la Hechicera Serpentina Aspheera.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Historia Antigua
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: El Equipo Exit
added.description: Los Fantásticos compiten por el número de visitas en sus videos con un equipo rival llamado "El equipo Exit" en una batalla donde se juegan el todo por el todo.

added.title: El Club de Exploradores
added.description: El ninja debe entrar en el Club del Explorador para obtener el segundo Pergamino de Spinjitzu Prohibido, en conflicto con el gerente del club y los miembros furiosos del club.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Perdidas y Ganancias
added.description: Un promotor llamado Everett Ray quiere convencer a Los Fantásticos de ingresar a una liga oficial de Batallas Bakugan.

added.title: Puffdora's Box
added.description: When Blossom gets overzealous with the spring cleaning, she accidentally unleashes a group of evil spirits.

added.title: Sr. Luna
added.description: Wynton encuentra un nuevo Bakugan que resulta difícil de controlar, y las cosas se complican cuando el Coronel Tripp se apodera de Trox.

added.title: Que Ocurre con Dan
added.description: Cuando Dan se comporta de forma extraña con los Fantásticos, Lightning olfatea la verdad: iUn impostor!

added.title: Leyendas del Senor Gar
added.description: Rad y Enid recuerdan la época en la que comenzaron a trabajar en el almacén y entendieron lo fabuloso que es el Sr. Gar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: Una Necesidad Inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: Mascara de Poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: Una Verdad a Medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Huyendo de Casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un Verdadero Lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Aterrizaje mocoso
added.description: A Beth se le atascan los muebles del diorama de Courtney en la nariz y Courtney tiene que recuperarlos antes de que llegue el juez del concurso de dioramas.

added.title: Baile en La Plaza
added.description: Cuando Rad organiza su propia fiesta de graduación en la Plaza, K.O. intenta asegurarse de que no haya ninguna complicación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Plaza Prom
added.description: When Rad throws his own prom at the Plaza, KO tries to makes sure it goes off without a hitch.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Courtney debe pasar todo el día sin corregir a sus amigos, y eso es difícil porque lo hacen todo mal.

added.title: Una bomba para lamer
added.description: Sin querer, Owen y Noah se convierten en magnates de las galletas y deben ocultar el ingrediente secreto, que es la saliva que deja Owen al lamerse las chispas.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Secret Swapper of Doom
added.description: When the girls get a Paper Fortune Teller that can predict the future if they tell it a secret, they begin to rely on it to predict everything. But when it predicts the Powerpuff Girls will be destroyed, the girls must find a way to stop the future from happening.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: King Axel
added.description: After a screening of the King Arthur tale, Axel holds out his sword and declares himself king, but when Dynamo uses his magnetism to steal the weapon and bestow it upon Masko, it casts doubt among the team over who is the true leader.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: The Trojan Bear
added.description: When Axel opens a subscription gift-box he didn't even order, the team finds their ranks divided by a robotic bear - or Princess SugarSalt in disguise!

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: All Play and No Work
added.description: Mega Man must resist the influence of a prankster bot named Chaotique, whose devil may care ideology appeals to the overworked superhero, until his friends pay the price for his dalliances.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: More More More!
added.description: In order to out-muscle Guts Man, Mega Man copies the big bot's schematics, and his insatiable appetite!

added.title: Snow Month
added.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Tomemonos un momento
added.description: El Sr. Gar y Carol se enfrentan a un villano de su pasado.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Too Much Is Never Enough

added.title: Let's Take a Moment
added.description: Mr. Gar and Carol fight a villain from their past.

added.title: The Bluster Bunch
added.description: A trail of tornadic destruction leads Mega Man, Suna, and Rush through a series of encounters with Air Man's quirky siblings.

added.title: And Then There Was Ben
added.description: Professor Paradox unites the good Bens from across all dimensions to take on Vilgax, Eon, and the evil Bens in the ultimate showdown!

added.title: Charm School
added.description: At Gwen's college, Ben suspects a new teacher and new student are old enemies.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: Companeros de Cama Extranos

added.title: Rey Axel
added.description: Después de una proyección de la historia del Rey Arturo, Axel extiende su espada y se declara rey, pero cuando Dynamo usa su magnetismo para robar el arma y dársela a Masko, arroja dudas entre el equipo sobre quién es el verdadero líder.

added.title: La Captura de Colosal
added.description: Colosal se cansa de sus responsabilidades en el cuartel general de sheriff y decide unirse a los Piratas del Cielo.

added.title: El Oso Troyano
added.description: Cuando Axel abre una caja de regalo de suscripción que ni siquiera ordenó, el equipo encuentra sus filas divididas por un oso robótico, io la Princesa SugarSalt disfrazada!
